latestPosts.caption:
If you ask me, the hospital might have had some of the greatest food in the world. My tastebuds were completely shut down because of the procedure, so don’t take my word for it on this one.

Thank you to my family for helping me keep my mind off of being stuck in a hospital bed by filming these videos. And thank you all for watching and for giving me motivation to keep making content. I appreciate you!

It’s a big day with my pituitary tumor surgery taking place! This is a procedure that will hopefully provide a surgical cure to my acromegaly - a disease that is causing my body to produce too much growth hormone. It’s been a chaotic few months between being diagnosed and preparing for this day but my family and I are so happy to finally be here.

I’ll be updating everyone after the procedure once I’m able to speak in complete sentences again.

Thank you for all the positivity and support!

When you think San Diego, do you think of fish tacos?  We spent an afternoon down in Ocean Beach and stopped at Blue Water Seafood to see what their $5 happy hour grilled fish taco was about!

If anyone’s got a favorite fish taco spot either in SD or  elsewhere, please let us know!

Thanks for watching and we’ll see you in the next one! Have an amazing day!
Running it back with these Rice Krispies Treats ice cream sandwiches | This taste test costed $7.56 and was found at Walmart

We needed something tasty after a bunch of pre-op lab work and found a small cafe in Anaheim! They had some fantastic waffles and chilaquiles with house made salsa verde! It’s always great to stumble into a small business and feel like you found a gem.

The restaurant is called The Brunch Cafe in Anaheim, CA and our meal totaled $31. Money well spent!

These are the best gourmet cookies in OC 🍪 From @dolcebytina in Irvine | Would you try these? 

We got 6 flavors:

Almond Croissant
Biscoff Cookie Butter
Chocolate Chip Walnut
Cookies and Cream
Pistachio Kunafah
S’mores

Everything was incredibly fresh and decadent! These are such high quality cookies and we think you’ll love them

Is this the best Thai restaurant in SoCal? Manaao is open is Tustin, and also coming soon to the Irvine Spectrum

We loved the authentic flavors here! We have Thai food at least a couple times a month and this restaurant stood out above the others.

Marugame Udon isn’t new to the noodle world, but they are new to Irvine! Now open in Diamond Jamboree. The noodles have a bouncy consistency that is just delicious!

If you want something a little different than brothy soup, try their nikutama udon. It’s served in a more concentrated liquid that has a punch of flavor and it’s one of our favorites.

Have you tried this place? What do you think of it?
